Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the veg has softened, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir in the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Stir in the @risotto rice{175%g} and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @water{600%ml} for the risotto, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @wild mushroom paste{15%g} to the ovenproof pan. Stir well to combine.

Bring back to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir in the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and @butter{30%g}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Spoon your risotto into #bowls{}.

Break up the @goat's cheese{75%g} and scatter over the risotto.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!